dbusreceipt makes nTPV to enable the receipt saving functions.
When dbusreceipt is launched, nTPV can load and save receipts.

dbusreceipt also communicate with nTPV POS systems to syncronize
receipts between POS. Whith dbusreceipt a waiter can load a receipt
that has been created at a remote nTPV POS.
(see /etc/dcopreceipt_config.xml)

dbusreceipt also needs an xml description file to define the lounges
at the restaurant. This file is also autoexplicative, you can find it
at /etc/ntpv/lounges.xml.

This module was previously a closed module.
